sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as React Client
    participant WS as WebSocket Handler
    participant REST as REST API
    participant DB as SQLite (slug-keyed)

    rect rgb(240, 220, 220)
        note over UI,DB: BEFORE (legacy path — now deleted)
        UI->>REST: GET /api/saves?genre=X&world=Y&player=Z
        REST->>DB: open saves/X/Y/Z/save.db
        DB-->>REST: snapshot
        REST-->>UI: { saves: [...] }
        UI->>WS: connect { genre_slug, world_slug, player_name }
        WS->>DB: db_path_for_session(genre, world, player)
        DB-->>WS: snapshot
        WS-->>UI: game state
    end

    rect rgb(220, 240, 220)
        note over UI,DB: AFTER (slug-only path)
        UI->>REST: POST /api/games
        REST-->>UI: { game_slug: "swift-dragon-42" }
        UI->>WS: connect { game_slug: "swift-dragon-42" }
        WS->>DB: db_path_for_slug("swift-dragon-42")
        DB-->>WS: snapshot (or None → first connect)
        alt first connect (saved is None)
            WS-->>UI: opening scene narration
        else resume
            WS-->>UI: resume from last save
        end
    end